t (Berkshire), or Westcote in (Gloucestershire, Hampshire, and Warwickshire)."],"variants":[{"name":"Wescott","meanings":["English (southwestern): variant of   Westcott  ."]},{"name":"Wescoat","meanings":["English: variant of   Westcott  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Westcott of La Vallee, Surrey was born in 1268, in Dorking, Surrey, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs. William Westcott in 1291, in Dorking, Surrey, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1268–":"1268–Surnud","1272–Female":"1272–Surnud","1292–Female":"1292–Surnud","1268–Male":"1268–Surnud","1268":"1268","1272":"1272","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","Dorking, Mole Valley, Surrey, England":"Dorking, Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1268–":"1268–Kuollut","1272–Female":"1272–Kuollut","1292–Female":"1292–Kuollut","1268–Male":"1268–Kuollut","1268":"1268","1272":"1272","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","Dorking, Mole Valley, Surrey, England":"Dorking, Surrey, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1268–":"1268–Décédé","1272–Female":"1272–Décédée","1292–Female":"1292–Décédée","1268–Male":"1268–Décédé","1268":"1268","1272":"1272","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","Dorking, Mole Valley, Surrey, England":"Dorkin